Roughly £14m of the £17m in donations received by the Conservative Parties this year has been from individuals and businesses. This shouldn't be too surprising - public funding is mainly available for the opposition party through the "Short Money" system.

## Raincloud or something


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
p <- don_by_party_indiv %>% 
  filter(Party_Name == "Conservative",
         grepl("Individual|Company",DonorStatus)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(Value,DonorStatus,label=DonorName,fill=DonorStatus)) +
  geom_jitter(alpha=0.7,size=2.5) +
  facet_wrap(~DonorStatus,scales="free",nrow = 2) +
  scale_x_continuous(label=comma) +
  labs(title = "XYZ")+
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(plot.title.position = "plot",
        legend.position = "none")


ggplotly(p)
```

